<style>
  h2 {
    width: 80vw;
  }
  p {
    width: 75vmin;
  }
</style>

//Instead of using px or em, you can use another relative metric called "viewport units"//
//The options are: % viewport width (vw), % viewport height (vh), % smallest dimension (vmin), % largest dimension (vmax)//
//In this example, h2's width is set to 80% of the viewport width//
//P's width is set to 75% of the smallest viewport dimension (height vs width)//
